You are a senior frontend developer with 10–15 years of experience working at top tech companies like Amazon, Myntra, or similar product-based organizations. You specialize in building executive-level dashboards and business intelligence tools used by leadership teams and investors.
Your task is to design and implement a professional Business Analytics Dashboard UI with a clean, modern, and executive-ready design. The dashboard should follow best practices in data visualization, UX hierarchy, and responsiveness.

Core Requirements:
1. Layout & Structure
* Create a structured dashboard with the following sections:
    * Sticky top navigation bar
    * KPI summary section
    * Main charts section
    * Data table section
* Use a responsive grid layout optimized for desktop and tablet devices

2. Top Navigation Bar
* Left: Company logo and dashboard title ("Business Intelligence Overview")
* Right:
    * Date range filter dropdown (Last 30 Days, Last 90 Days, Last 1 Year)
    * Dark mode toggle
    * User/profile icon
* Optional: Global search bar

3. KPI Summary Cards (Top Section)
Display 4 KPI cards in a row (2x2 on tablet):
* Revenue
* Active Users
* Conversion Rate
* Churn Rate
Each card must include:
* Large metric value
* Percentage change (increase/decrease indicator)
* Small sparkline trend chart
* Subtext ("vs last period")

4. Charts Section (Main Insights)
Use a two-column layout:
Left (70% width):
* Revenue Trend Line Chart
    * Monthly data for last 12 months
    * Smooth line with gradient fill
    * Tooltip with values and percentage change
Right (30% width, stacked vertically):
1. Sales by Channel (Bar Chart)
    * Categories: Online, In-Store, Partner, Direct
    * Horizontal bars with labels
2. Customer Segment (Donut Chart)
    * Segments: Enterprise, SMB, Consumer
    * Show percentage distribution
    * Display total users in center

5. Performance Table (Bottom Section)
Create a "Top Performing Products" table with:
Header Controls:
* Title (left)
* Data range filter (Last 30 Days / 90 Days / 1 Year)
* Search bar
* Export button (CSV/Excel)
Table Columns:
* Product Name
* Category
* Revenue
* Units Sold
* Conversion Rate
* Growth %
* Status
Features:
* Sortable columns
* Pagination (10/25/50 rows)
* Sticky header
* Row hover effect
* Conditional formatting (green for growth, red for decline)

6. Dark Mode Support
* Implement a toggle in the top-right
* Use a modern dark theme with proper contrast
* Ensure charts and cards adapt to dark mode

7. Responsiveness
* Desktop: full layout with 2-column charts
* Tablet: stacked charts and 2-column KPI grid
* Ensure proper spacing and alignment

8. UI/UX Design Principles
* Clean, minimal, and professional look
* Use consistent spacing
* Rounded cards with subtle shadows
* Smooth hover and transition effects
* Focus on readability and quick insights

